      "flags": {},
      "order": 1,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "title": "How Progress Is Reported",
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "WHAT IS PINNED\n\nQwen sees two ordered images: first, then last. Both are center-cropped to the selected geometry. The Wan VAE encodes each endpoint independently. The sampler restores the clean first latent and clean final latent after every scheduler step, while all middle latents denoise normally with global attention."
      ],
      "color": "#243447",
      "bgcolor": "#182433"
    },
    {
      "id": 9,
      "type": "MarkdownNote",
      "pos": [
        843.2222222222279,
        1706.6527777777644
      ],
      "size": [
        429.12847483095584,
        104.86685032139826
      ],
      "flags": {},
      "order": 2,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "title": "Prompt Rules (Important)",
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "PROMPTING FOR A BRIDGE\n\nState one continuous action from image A to image B. Describe how pose, camera, objects, and lighting change over time. Avoid vague prompts, cuts, teleportation, dramatic angle changes, or endpoints that depict different identities. The two endpoint previews show the exact crops being constrained."
      ],
      "color": "#4b2a2a",
      "bgcolor": "#301b1b"
    },
    {
      "id": 7,
      "type": "MarkdownNote",
      "pos": [
        846.666666666657,
        1871.8055555555409
      ],
      "size": [
        382.08333333333576,
        203.75000000000114
      ],
      "flags": {},
      "order": 3,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "title": "Quick Presets + Safe Experiment Order",
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "EXPERIMENTAL FLF QUICK START\n\nThis is not a native LingBot mode. The first latent and final latent are hard-pinned while LingBot generates the bridge.\n\n1. Choose closely related first and last images: same subject, scene, camera axis, and aspect ratio.\n2. Describe the exact motion connecting them.\n3. First test: 640×352, 20 FPS, 3 seconds, 24–30 steps, CFG 3, shift 3.\n4. Keep sequential_sage. Leave FlashVSR and RIFE off until the bridge works.\n5. Large viewpoint or identity changes may morph, freeze, or jump because LingBot was trained for first-frame TI2V, not FLF."
      ],
      "color": "#5b4615",
      "bgcolor": "#372b0e"
    },
